25/01/2007
MOSTAR, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Mostar Cantonal Court sentenced eight former members of the Bosniak BiH Army to a total of 17 years in prison on Wednesday (January 24th), for committing war crimes against Croats in 1993.
The victims were Croat prisoners of war and one civilian, held at a school prison camp run by the Bosniak military in Mostar.
(HRT, PBS BiH - 24/01/07)
